        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 3:44PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from over Garden City to 7 miles north of
Midway, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pooler, Richmond Hill, Coffee Bluff, Windsor Forest, Hunter Army
Airfield, I-16/I-95 Interchange, Midtown Savannah, Downtown
Savannah, Savannah International Airport and Wilmington Island.

This includes the following highways...
I-16 between mile markers 159 and 165.
I-95 in Georgia between mile markers 77 and 100.
I-516 between mile markers 3 and 6.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
